  "prompt": "Which laptop is best for an i5 with 4GB of RAM and 1TB hard disk configuration under the price of 25k?",
  "response": "As of the current available options, it's challenging to find a laptop with the specified configuration (i5 processor, 4GB RAM, and 1TB hard disk) under the price of \u20b925,000 (Indian Rupees) due to the cost of components, especially the i5 processor. However, you can look at budget laptops that closely match your requirements, potentially with an Intel i3 processor or an alternative specification that balances performance and price.\n\nHere are a few options you can consider:\n\n1. **ASUS VivoBook**: Known for providing good performance at a budget-friendly price, you might find models with slightly lower specifications but still offering decent performance for everyday tasks.\n\n2. **HP 15 Series**: HP occasionally offers laptops with a lower-end processor but with reliable build quality and decent specs that might fit within your budget range.\n\n3. **Acer Aspire**: Acer often has budget models with configurations that might fit within your price range. Look for an alternative processor like AMD Ryzen 3, which can offer comparable performance.\n\n4. **Lenovo Ideapad**: Lenovo's Ideapad series frequently includes budget-friendly models that could offer the combination you're looking for or something close to it.\n\n5. **Dell Inspiron 15**: Dell\u2019s Inspiron series often has budget-friendly options that might not have the exact specifications but can include a robust build and performance for the price.\n\nCheck the latest models online and compare specifications to find the best deal within your budget. Prices and availability fluctuate, so a recent model might fit your requirements closely.\n\nFor the most accurate and updated purchase advice, visit local electronics stores or check online marketplaces like Amazon, Flipkart, etc., to ensure compatibility with your needs while staying within budget.",
